<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN318-intro">
      <p type="edition">tiṇaiyum tuṟaiyum avai. peruṅkuṉṟūrkiḻār.
      </p>
      <p xml:lang="en" type="translation">  
      </p>
    </div>
    <div xml:id="PN318">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>koyyaṭaku vāṭat taruviṟa kuṇaṅka</l>
<l>mayilañ cāyaṉ māa yōḷoṭu</l>
<l>pacittaṉ ṟamma peruntakai yūrē</l>
<l>maṉaiyuṟai kurīik kaṟaiyaṇaṟ cēval</l>
<l>pāṇar narampiṉ cukiroṭu vayamāṉ</l>
<l>kuraṟcey pīliyi ṉiḻaitta kuṭampaip</l>
<l>peruñcey nelli ṉarici yārntutaṉ</l>
<l>puṉpuṟap peṭaiyoṭu vatiyum</l>
<l>yāṇart tākum vēntuviḻu muṟiṉē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>While the edible leaves that had been plucked fade [and] the firewood brought dries up</l>
<l>the village of the paragon along with the dark women</l>
<l>of peacock-like grace goes hungry, alas.</l>
<l>[A place] where the black-bearded males of the house-dwelling sparrow</l>
<l>feed together on grains of paddy from the big wet fields</l>
<l>[and] dwell together with [their] low-backed females</l>
<l>in [their] nests fashioned of curled-up lion(?) hair</l>
<l>and fibres from the strings of bards,</l>
<l>it will become fertile [again] when the king prevails.  </l>
</lg>
    </div>
  </body>
